	"Directions                                                                                In a large skillet, cook the meat, onion and green pepper over medium heat until meat is no longer pink; drain. Stir in macaroni, corn, soups and seasonings.                                                                                            Transfer to a greased 13-in. x 9-in. baking dish. Toss bread crumbs and butter; sprinkle over top. Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Uncover and bake 15 minutes longer or until heated through.                                        Yield: 12 servings.                                                                                                     After preparing a double batch of Potluck Hot Dish on the stove, transfer half to a 13- x 9- x 2-inch baking dish and sprinkle with buttered bread crumbs. Bake as directed. Freeze the reamining portiion in an airtight container. When ready to use, thaw, transfer to a 13- x 9- x 2-inch baking dish, sprinkle with buttered bread crumbs and bake as directed.                                                                                                Originally published as Potluck Hot Dish in  Taste of Home Ground Beef Cookbook1999, p250                                                                                                                                                                                                       Nutritional Facts                                                                             1 serving (1 cup) equals 301 calories, 13 g fat (6 g saturated fat), 51 mg cholesterol, 781 mg sodium, 27 g carbohydrate, 2 g fiber, 18 g protein.                                                                                                                                                                     Print                                                                                    Add to Recipe Box                            Email a Friend",
